  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "Music has a powerful way of tapping into our emotions, and certain songs resonate deeply enough to bring tears to our eyes. Whether it's due to poignant lyrics, moving melodies, or personal associations, here's a list of songs that many people find emotionally stirring:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton**\n   - Written after the tragic loss of Clapton's son, this heartfelt ballad explores themes of loss and longing.\n\n2. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen (and various covers)**\n   - Its beautiful melody and contemplative lyrics touch on love, loss, and spirituality, making it a tear-jerker for many.\n\n3. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele**\n   - Adele's powerful vocals combined with the song's themes of lost love and acceptance strike a deep emotional chord.\n\n4. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay**\n   - This song offers comfort and hope in the face of hardship and personal struggles, resonating with listeners going through tough times.\n\n5. **\"Everybody Hurts\" by R.E.M.**\n   - A reassuring anthem that acknowledges pain and encourages listeners to hold on, often providing solace during difficult moments.\n\n6. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron**\n   - Its haunting melody and lyrics about longing and regret make it a poignant choice for reflection and deep emotion.\n\n7. **\"My Heart Will Go On\" by Celine Dion**\n   - Known as the love theme from *Titanic*, this song evokes strong feelings of love and loss.\n\n8. **\"See You Again\" by Wiz Khalifa ft. Charlie Puth**\n   - Written as a tribute to the late actor Paul Walker, it captures themes of friendship and remembrance.\n\n9. **\"Yesterday\" by The Beatles**\n   - A melancholic reflection on lost love and the passage of time, delivered with The Beatles' signature melody.\n\n10. **\"Skinny Love\" by Bon Iver (or Birdy\u2019s cover)**\n    - Its raw and intimate lyrics combined with a minimalist arrangement create a deeply emotional listening experience.\n\n11. **\"Un-break My Heart\" by Toni Braxton**\n    - A powerful ballad about heartbreak and the desire to reverse the pain of lost love.\n\n12. **\"Everybody\u2019s Got to Learn Sometime\" by The Korgis (or Beck\u2019s cover)**\n    - This song's reflective lyrics and haunting melody often move listeners to tears.\n\n13. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston**\n    - A soulful farewell that beautifully conveys love and goodbye, showcased by Houston\u2019s exceptional vocals.\n\n14. **\"Fast Car\" by Tracy Chapman**\n    - A narrative song that tells a story of hope and struggle, touching on themes of escape and the pursuit of a better life.\n\n15. **\"Candle in the Wind\" by Elton John**\n    - Originally written in honor of Marilyn Monroe and later revised for Princess Diana, it's a tribute that captures loss and remembrance.\n\nRemember, the emotional impact of a song can be highly personal. What brings one person to tears might not affect another the same way. Exploring different genres and artists can help you find the songs that resonate most deeply with your own experiences and emotions.",
